The University of Louisville shall provide:
Upon approval of the Council on Postsecondary Education, associate and baccalaureate degree programs of instruction;
Upon approval of the Council on Postsecondary Education, master's-degree programs, specialist degrees above the master's-degree level, doctoral degree programs, and joint doctoral programs in cooperation with other public institutions of higher education;
Upon approval of the Council on Postsecondary Education, professional degree programs including medicine, dentistry, law, engineering, and social professions.
